<Layout
	title="About TWPA"
	description="True Wisdom Practitioners Association — cultivating mindful living through the timeless wisdom of the East."
	pubDate={new Date('2026-04-08')}
>
	<p>
		True Wisdom Practitioners Association (TWPA) is a welcoming space for all who are drawn to the
		timeless wisdom of the East. Based in Oceania, we bring together practitioners and curious minds
		to explore the depths of Buddhist and Chan teachings.
	</p>

	<h2>Our Mission</h2>
	<p>
		We are dedicated to upholding the authentic teachings of Buddhism, fostering peace of mind,
		and benefiting all sentient beings. Through lectures, workshops, and courses, we seek to make
		the wisdom of the Dharma widely accessible to all those with an affinity for it, guiding
		participants to embody Buddhist practice in their daily lives and deepen their understanding
		of Buddhism and Chan culture.
	</p>

	<h2>What We Explore</h2>
	<p>
		Our blog and community delve into topics that bridge ancient wisdom with modern life:
	</p>
	<ul>
		<li>Mindful living and meditation practices</li>
		<li>Plant-based wellness and conscious eating</li>
		<li>Emotional well-being through Buddhist psychology</li>
		<li>Chan (Zen) teachings and their practical application</li>
		<li>Community events, retreats, and dharma gatherings in Australia and New Zealand</li>
	</ul>

	<h2>Join Us</h2>
	<p>
		Whether you are a seasoned practitioner or simply curious about the path, you are welcome here.
		Subscribe to our newsletter to stay connected, or reach out to us at
		<a href="mailto:contact@twpa.info">contact@twpa.info</a>.
	</p>
</Layout>
